:"India Ratings reaffirmed Bank of India's Tier II and infra bond ratings at IND AA/Stable.\nIssuer rating and AT1 bonds withdrawn; reflects systemic importance, better capital, and govt support.","summary":"India Ratings reaffirmed Bank of India's Tier II and infra bond ratings at IND AA/Stable.\nIssuer rating and AT1 bonds withdrawn; reflects systemic importance, better capital, and govt support.","url":"https://sqst.in/shareMessage?msgId=807243932845716590","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T19:09:11","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"464212","title":"Nifty fell 2.96% to 24,571.75, Sensex dropped 2.88% to 79,899.42 due to STT hike, modest capex, and no major defense announcements.\nPSU banks like Bank of India and BoB declined; metals saw volatility, with silver down 9% and gold futures down 3%.","summary":"Nifty fell 2.96% to 24,571.75, Sensex dropped 2.88% to 79,899.42 due to STT hike, modest capex, and no major defense announcements.\nPSU banks like Bank of India and BoB declined; metals saw volatility, with silver down 9% and gold futures down 3%.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/nifty-sensex-crash-on-budget-day-stt-hike-to-modest-capex-heres-eight-reasons-why-10923972#publisher=newsstand","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T13:07:34","source":"NDTV Profit"},{"id":"464173","title":"PSU Bank stocks fell sharply after Budget 2026 due to record borrowing of ₹17.2 lakh crore by the government.\nBank of India, Indian Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, and Bank of Baroda lost 5-6% amid treasury loss concerns.","summary":"PSU Bank stocks fell sharply after Budget 2026 due to record borrowing of ₹17.2 lakh crore by the government.\nBank of India, Indian Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, and Bank of Baroda lost 5-6% amid treasury loss concerns.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/explained-why-psu-banks-sold-off-sharply-after-the-union-budget-2026-19838606.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T12:51:09","source":"CNBC TV 18"},{"id":"464223","title":"PSU bank shares, including Bank of India, Bank of Baroda, and Indian Bank, dropped after FM Nirmala Sitharaman proposed a banking review panel.\nThe panel aims to assess reforms for growth, financial stability, inclusion, and restructuring NBFCs like PFC and REC for efficiency.","summary":"PSU bank shares, including Bank of India, Bank of Baroda, and Indian Bank, dropped after FM Nirmala Sitharaman proposed a banking review panel.\nThe panel aims to assess reforms for growth, financial stability, inclusion, and restructuring NBFCs like PFC and REC for efficiency.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/budget-2026-bank-of-india-bank-of-baroda-and-indian-bank-shares-slide-as-psu-banks-decline-after-proposal-for-banking-review-panel-10923936#publisher=newsstand","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T12:40:05","source":"NDTV Profit"},{"id":"260201144049186","title":"Union Bank of India and Bank of India may merge by year-end, creating the second-largest PSU bank with assets of ₹25.4 lakh crore in FY25.\nThe merged entity would rank sixth in market cap at ₹2.13 lakh crore, surpassing Canara Bank and PNB, but faces tech integration challenges.","summary":"Union Bank of India and Bank of India may merge by year-end, creating the second-largest PSU bank with assets of ₹25.4 lakh crore in FY25.\nThe merged entity would rank sixth in market cap at ₹2.13 lakh crore, surpassing Canara Bank and PNB, but faces tech integration challenges.","url":"https://www.financialexpress.com/business/banking-finance-unionbank-of-india-bank-of-india-may-merge-by-year-end-4125302/","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-31T09:31:00","source":"Financial Express"},{"id":"804333690898879616","title":"Bank of India redeemed ₹750 crore Additional Tier I Bonds Series VI on call date.\nRedemption included ₹56.1 crore interest; no outstanding amount remains.","summary":"Bank of India redeemed ₹750 crore Additional Tier I Bonds Series VI on call date.\nRedemption included ₹56.1 crore interest; no outstanding amount 